          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "UNFLD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " From  experimental   spectra   of   scattered",
                " photons  peak  centroids  and  areas  were extracted",
                " using the computer program  'sampo'.  The  centroids",
                " were   converted   to   energies   using   a  linear",
                " calibration based on  five  levels  (from  2.125  to",
                " 8.920  MeV)  strongly  excited  in photon scattering",
                " from B-11.  The scattering yields were converted  to",
                " cross  sections  using an empirical determination of",
                " the product of incident photon  intensity  with  the",
                " detector efficiency."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors  only.  Systematic  errors",
                " are estimated to be no larger than 8%,  arising from",
                " uncertainties in the photon flux  (5%),  geometrical",
                " factor (5%), atomic absorption coefficient (3%), and",
                " photon energy (1%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Resonant photon   scattering   from  Fe-56  has  been",
                " measured from 5 to 10 MeV using Ge(Li) detector  and",
                " bremsstrahlung  beams with end-point energies of 7.6",
                " and 10.3 MeV.  Average elastic and inelastic (to the",
                " first   excited   state)   photon  scattering  cross",
                " sections were measured from 5.8 to 11.5 MeV (i.e. to",
                " above neutron threshold)."
              ]
            }
          ],
